Popcon Asia is finally over and i've got to say that it was a very rewarding experience. Being there with countless creators and visitors still made me nervous. But thanks to my good fellas at @epiphany.id , especially the bois @alvadomdom @kensutanza @ryan.oktav also @hanjip, we can break through it and gave our best. I can't thank enough of those wonderful people that i met, who shared their time to speak, get to know each other and supporting each other. We learned, and shared a lot of stuff during this past days.

As a token of appreciation also (to warm up my drawing hand) i will do series of character design based on popcon people that i met. 
Thanks again for those supporting our works! üíõüíôüíúüíö

üë∞

Marriage.
Force marriages.
Under-age marriages.

It may seem to be a tradition to some people, it may rubs you right, marriages always seems like the GO to options for some youth nowadays heck even the old days.
I personally believe, each one of us both man and woman have a dream and can achieve it if we fight for it and never give up.

But truth be told, some girls even women can't achieve the same privelege of that just because some people still sees them merely as an object. A trophy to win for your family. Marriage now seems more like an achievement for their boys and girls. You haven't married yet just because you wanna work hard for your dream? Newsflash! Some families even friends might roll their eyes on you. And i truly believe the pressure on this matters for Women is harder than men.

Also, this poem was delivered by Emi Mahmoud. She's a poet that won the 2015 Individual World Poetry Championship. As i was working on finalizing my animation, i stumbled across her speech on this subject and it moved me. So as a token of appreciation, i decided to include her poem into my animation! ‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§ Thankyou!
